      en: "Of the Zuhra clan of Quraysh, the maternal relatives of the Prophet ﷺ, who proudly said: 'This is my maternal uncle — let any man show me his!' Converted at seventeen, among the very first. The first man to shoot an arrow for the cause of Allah; at Uhud the Prophet told him 'Shoot, may my father and mother be your ransom!' — having joined both parents for no one else. His mother vowed to stop eating until he left Islam, and the verse commanding kindness to parents (without obeying them in sin) was revealed about him. Famous for having his supplications answered (al-mustajab ad-da'wa), the Prophet having prayed for him. One of the six of the Shura council. Supreme commander at Al-Qadisiyya (636) which shattered the Persian empire, then the capture of Ctesiphon (al-Mada'in); he founded the city of Kufa. Last of the ten promised Paradise to die, in his palace at al-'Aqiq near Medina, buried at al-Baqi'.",
